Hi,
# Context

I'm using React.js

We can use `require("react")", or`require("react/addons")` if we need access to React + some additional addons.

addons.js looks like:

```
var React = require("./React");
React.addons = ...
module.exports = React;
```

My app is bundled in 2 parts using Browserify require/external: `app.js` and `appLibs.js`.

My app uses `atom-react` which is a library that has a peerDependency on `react` and that uses React with addons (ie uses `require("react/addons")`)

My app code also uses React with addons.

Here's a simplified build setting used:

```
var libs = [
    "atom-react",
    "react",
    ... other libs
];

gulp.task('browserify-libs', function () {
    var b = browserify(...);
    libs.forEach(function(lib) {
        b.require(lib);
    });
    return b.bundle().......
});
gulp.task('browserify',['browserify-libs'],function () {
    var b = browserify(...);
    libs.forEach(function(lib) {
        b.external(lib);
    });
    return b.bundle().......
});
```
# Problem

This setting does not work well because there are `require("react/addons")` statements in both the my app code (shipped in `app.js`) and atom-react shipped in `appLib.js`

The result is that `react/addons` is bundled in both files `app.js` and `appLibs.js`, and it is the same for `react`, and this makes the React framework fail miserably.
# Workaround

A workaround is to use:

```
var libs = [
    "atom-react",
    "react",
    "react/addons",
    ... other libs
];
```

This way, `react/addons` is also excluded from `app.js` and React will only be packaged in `app.js`
# Proposed solution

I think calling `b.exclude("react")` should also exclude nested packages and automatically exclude `react/addons`

And calling b.require("react") should probably also permits to call `require("react/addons")`

